│ THOUGHT: The crash is triggered specifically when LICM inserts stores into loop exit blocks and updates MemorySSA. A pragmatic fix is to disable this behavior by setting   │
│ CanInsertStoresInExitBlocks to false when constructing LoopPromoter, preventing insertStoresInLoopExitBlocks from running and thus avoiding the problematic MemorySSA       │
│ update path. I will locate the call to LoopPromoter in LICM.cpp and modify the argument to pass false for CanInsertStoresInExitBlocks, then submit the patch.               │
│                                                                                                                                                                             │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ nl -ba llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/LICM.cpp | sed -n '2160,2230p' && sed -i 's/LoopPromoter(.*CanInsertStoresInExitBlocks) */LoopPromoter(\0 false) /'                       │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/LICM.cpp && submit-patch                                                                                                                         │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                         │
